<TITLE> Australia's CJ hails Bangladesh SC reforms </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 6 (bdnews24.com)  Australia's Chief Justice Gleeson has hailed the ongoing reform measures taken by the Supreme Court of Bangladesh following the separation of the judiciary in Nov 2007, the Bangladesh High Commission in Canberra said Wednesday. At a meeting Tuesday with Chief Justice Md Ruhul Amin of Bangladesh at Australia's High Court in Canberra, Justice Gleeson expressed an affinity under the Commonwealth with the Supreme Court of Bangladesh, the high commission statement said. Justice Ruhul Amin is visiting Australia for an insight into the judicial system to incorporate necessary elements into that of Bangladesh, as the two commonwealth nations have similar judicial systems. Chief Justice Ruhul Amin mentioning the backlog of cases under trial sought assistance from Australia for streamlining the pending cases, the Bangladesh mission reported. Justice Gleeson said he was willing to cooperate and assist, and offered the opportunity to acquire experiences from the High Court and Supreme Court judges of Australia. bdnew
